Think about it this way,

00:19:15.486 --> 00:19:17.923
let's say HBO decided
they wanted to cancel this show,

00:19:18.023 --> 00:19:20.925
their hand would be pretty weak
if I was able to get around that

00:19:21.025 --> 00:19:22.460
simply by changing the name to

00:19:22.560 --> 00:19:25.764
<i> "Earlier Times but Now
Starring Spance Mörgendörffer."</i>

00:19:25.864 --> 00:19:26.965
(AUDIENCE LAUGHS, APPLAUDS)

00:19:27.065 --> 00:19:29.834
And it is true that China
could increase

00:19:29.934 --> 00:19:32.504
enforcement of its sanctions,
but they are understandably

00:19:32.604 --> 00:19:34.439
worried about
where that could lead.

00:19:35.073 --> 00:19:37.175 line:0%
What they worry about is,
if they do that,

00:19:37.275 --> 00:19:38.676 line:0%
will the regime collapse?

00:19:39.110 --> 00:19:41.246 line:0%
What does that mean?
Millions of refugees

00:19:41.346 --> 00:19:44.683 line:0%
pouring into China, uh,
possibly a unified Korea,

00:19:44.783 --> 00:19:46.651 line:0%
that is then a
Pro-American country

00:19:46.851 --> 00:19:48.587 line:0%
sitting on their southern border
where, don't forget,

00:19:48.687 --> 00:19:51.456 line:0%
there are 30,000 American
troops in South Korea,

00:19:51.556 --> 00:19:53.191 line:0%
which would then be
on China's border,

00:19:53.291 --> 00:19:55.193 line:0%
and by the way,
15 nuclear weapons.

00:19:55.726 --> 00:19:58.530
You know that there are a lot
of problems when you end up

00:19:58.630 --> 00:20:01.599
saying, "Oh, and by the way,
15 nuclear weapons."

00:20:02.033 --> 00:20:04.136
Imagine you were a babysitter
and you heard,

00:20:04.236 --> 00:20:06.705
"Okay, you've got his EpiPen,
you know about his nut allergy,

00:20:06.805 --> 00:20:09.040
he needs his inhaler every hour,
oh, and by the way,

00:20:09.140 --> 00:20:10.908
he has 15 nuclear weapons."

00:20:11.008 --> 00:20:12.176
(AUDIENCE LAUGHING)

00:20:12.276 --> 00:20:14.812
Now Trump has also been
mentioning military solutions,

00:20:14.912 --> 00:20:17.682
but even targeted strikes
against weapons systems

00:20:17.782 --> 00:20:19.918
could get out of hand very fast.

00:20:20.218 --> 00:20:22.087
North Korea would likely
retaliate and they have

00:20:22.187 --> 00:20:25.657
an estimated 8,000 pieces
of heavy artillery stationed

00:20:25.757 --> 00:20:28.226
just north of the DMZ,
which is here.

00:20:28.493 --> 00:20:30.729
And that artillery is capable
of reaching Seoul,

00:20:30.829 --> 00:20:32.397
which is just 40 miles away,

00:20:32.497 --> 00:20:35.166
and is an area
with 25 million people.

00:20:35.266 --> 00:20:39.071
So, even a non-nuclear war could
have horrific results.

00:20:39.271 --> 00:20:41.773
And, let's just engage
in some truly magical thinking.

00:20:41.873 --> 00:20:44.976
What if you could somehow
just take out Kim Jong-un?

00:20:45.277 --> 00:20:48.313
Well, you've probably got
an immediate humanitarian crisis

00:20:48.413 --> 00:20:50.415
on your hands,
as well as a leaderless country

00:20:50.515 --> 00:20:52.683
with a power vacuum
and nuclear weapons.

00:20:52.950 --> 00:20:55.120
And, as we've learned from Iraq
and Afghanistan,

00:20:55.220 --> 00:20:57.589
when regimes fall
and there's no plan in place,

00:20:57.689 --> 00:21:00.191
that vacuum can be filled
with terrible things.

00:21:00.525 --> 00:21:04.629
We do not want to find out what
North Korea's ISIS would be.

00:21:04.963 --> 00:21:07.732
Even just the phrase,
"North Korea's ISIS"

00:21:07.832 --> 00:21:09.567
is absolutely terrifying.

00:21:09.934 --> 00:21:12.303
It's like saying,
"9/11's Bill Cosby."

00:21:12.503 --> 00:21:16.708
-(AUDIENCE LAUGHING)
-What would that even be? I hope
we never have to find out.

00:21:17.642 --> 00:21:21.012
So, sanctions are no guarantee
and military action could be

00:21:21.112 --> 00:21:23.815
catastrophic and diplomacy is
going to be extremely difficult,

00:21:23.915 --> 00:21:27.085
given that you usually need to
have a specific goal in mind,

00:21:27.185 --> 00:21:30.255
and Trump seems to be making
all of this up as he goes along.

00:21:30.889 --> 00:21:32.790 line:0%
We are learning
stunning new details about

00:21:32.890 --> 00:21:35.894 line:0%
President Trump's extraordinary
"fire and fury" threat tonight,

00:21:36.127 --> 00:21:38.697 line:0%
multiple sources telling CNN
the president ad-libbed

00:21:38.797 --> 00:21:41.299 line:0%
those words, they were
improvised, on the fly.

00:21:41.833 --> 00:21:45.803
For fuck's sake!
That is just not a good idea.

00:21:45.903 --> 00:21:49.941
As I'm sure someone
has had to say to Wayne Brady
at a funeral more than once,

00:21:50.242 --> 00:21:52.944
"Now is not a good time
to improvise."

00:21:53.044 --> 00:21:53.878
(AUDIENCE LAUGHING)

00:21:53.978 --> 00:21:55.714
Here's a one-word suggestion,
Wayne,

00:21:55.814 --> 00:21:58.016
"Mourn, mourn like a person.

00:21:58.717 --> 00:22:01.185
And look, the thing is
that's not a surprise!

00:22:01.386 --> 00:22:03.888
Deep down, we all assumed that
he was winging it.

00:22:03.988 --> 00:22:06.157
We have become accustomed
to discounting

00:22:06.257 --> 00:22:08.626
a large percentage
of what comes out of his face.

00:22:08.726 --> 00:22:11.362
But North Korea is listening
to what he says.

00:22:11.462 --> 00:22:14.132
And the people there
have been primed for decades

00:22:14.232 --> 00:22:16.567
to believe that America
is on the brink of an invasion.

00:22:16.934 --> 00:22:18.603
Just look at their
government's response

00:22:18.703 --> 00:22:20.238
to his "fire and fury" line.

